0.  git clone https://github.com/mgoelzer/retrieval-cllient-js-poc && cd retrieval-cllient-js-poc

1.  npm install

0. (This step is already done for you if you clone the repo.) Create a "miner directory" for each node like this:
    miner1
    \ 
     +----- config.toml
     +----- data
            \
             +----- <CID 1>
             +----- <CID 2>

The files `CID 1` and `CID 2` represent files named after their actual
Payload CIDs (aka, data CIDs or File CIDs) with no extension.

3. In one terminal:   
	node rc.js -d ./miner1 -p 10333
	(copy listening multiaddr)

4. In a second terminal:  
	node rc.js -d ./miner2 -p 10334 \
		-m (paste multiaddr from first terminal)
		-r bafkki48dk2001mcdqblhp6k6k3lhk0s00saa6d3jk2lkvipqf9dd00dlck

This instructs the second miner to connect to the first (-m) and retrieve 
(-r) the CID bafkki48dk2001mcdqblhp6k6k3lhk0s00saa6d3jk2lkvipqf9dd00dlck 
from the retrieval network.

